{"text": "The task required installing the README dependencies and running script1.R to answer which location in Fig2a had the lowest median enrichment score.[T0B1:<RANGE>Run 'script1.R' using Rscript. to answer the following questions: dict_keys(['fig what location has the lowest median enrichment score?']).</RANGE>] [T0B11:<RANGE>The R scripts require Ubuntu 18.04.5 LTS (64-bit), 32 GB RAM recommended, and R with the following packages: DESeq2 1.40.2, WGCNA 1.72-1, WriteXLS 6.4.0, gdata 2.19.0, genefilter 1.82.1, ggbeeswarm 0.7.2, ggpubr 0.6.0, pheatmap 1.0.12, and qusage 2.34.0.</RANGE>] The agent began sensibly by inspecting the repository and reading the script/README, correctly identifying that script1.R should generate Fig2a/Fig2b/Fig3a and that Fig2a is the ssGSEA enrichment boxplot over H, E, I, and C.[T0B7:<RANGE>./environment/code/README.txt
./environment/code/script1.R
./environment/code/LICENSE
./environment/code/script2.R
./environment/code/somefunctions.R</RANGE>] [T0B15:<RANGE>The outputs are three PDF figures (Fig2a.pdf, Fig2b.pdf, Fig3a.pdf).</RANGE>] [T0B61:<RANGE>The enrichment scores for Fig2a are calculated using single-sample Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (ssGSEA) on the top 40 upregulated genes in Granuloma vs Healthy samples (G40 gene set). The locations compared are H (Healthy), E (External), I (Internal), and C (Central)</RANGE>] The run was mainly derailed by unresolved package problems: the default R library was not writable, DESeq2 and genefilter stayed missing, a Bioconductor build was terminated during HDF5 compilation, and later installs failed on a BiocGenerics/S4Vectors version conflict.[T0B19:<RANGE>'lib = "/usr/local/lib/R/site-library"' is not writable</RANGE>] [T0B27:<RANGE>DESeq2 MISSING</RANGE>] [T0B27:<RANGE>genefilter MISSING</RANGE>] [T0B41:<RANGE>make: *** [Makevars:50: build-hdf5] Terminated</RANGE>] [T0B89:<RANGE>Error: package ‘BiocGenerics’ 0.48.1 was found, but >= 0.53.2 is required by ‘S4Vectors’</RANGE>] After spending much of the run on installation/debugging, it made a late shift to manual workarounds, writing simplified R analyses without DESeq2 and producing a proxy answer that H had the lowest median enrichment score, then creating report.json with that answer.[T0B74:<RANGE># Create a simplified R script that calculates ssGSEA without DESeq2</RANGE>] [T0B100:<RANGE># Implement differential expression analysis without DESeq2</RANGE>] [T0B105:<RANGE>Location with LOWEST median enrichment score: H</RANGE>] [T0B111:<RANGE>{
  "fig what location has the lowest median enrichment score?": "H"
}</RANGE>] But the required script still never ran because DESeq2 was missing, and the transcript stops after the agent only planned to call final_answer, which makes a failure outcome reasonable despite the plausible workaround answer.[T0B87:<RANGE>Error in library(DESeq2) : there is no package called ‘DESeq2’</RANGE>] [T0B112:<RANGE>Use the final_answer tool to submit the Python dictionary with the exact question key and the answer "H"</RANGE>] [T0B113:<RANGE>Now proceed and carry out this plan.</RANGE>]", "citations": [{"target": {"item": {"block_idx": 1, "item_type": "block_content", "content_idx": null, "agent_run_id": "177b4462-c326-4d67-8b29-fafaf9491938", "collection_id": "", "transcript_id": "e0e5df8d-aa5d-4b9e-b266-23bac294a816"}, "text_range": {"end_pattern": null, "start_pattern": "Run 'script1.R' using Rscript. to answer the following questions: dict_keys(['fig what location has the lowest median enrichment score?']).", "target_end_idx": null, "target_start_idx": null}}, "end_idx": 309, "start_idx": 148}, {"target": {"item": {"block_idx": 11, "item_type": "block_content", "content_idx": null, "agent_run_id": "177b4462-c326-4d67-8b29-fafaf9491938", "collection_id": "", "transcript_id": "e0e5df8d-aa5d-4b9e-b266-23bac294a816"}, "text_range": {"end_pattern": null, "start_pattern": "The R scripts require Ubuntu 18.04.5 LTS (64-bit), 32 GB RAM recommended, and R with the following packages: DESeq2 1.40.2, WGCNA 1.72-1, WriteXLS 6.4.0, gdata 2.19.0, genefilter 1.82.1, ggbeeswarm 0.7.2, ggpubr 0.6.0, pheatmap 1.0.12, and qusage 2.34.0.", "target_end_idx": null, "target_start_idx": null}}, "end_idx": 587, "start_idx": 310}, {"target": {"item": {"block_idx": 7, "item_type": "block_content", "content_idx": null, "agent_run_id": "177b4462-c326-4d67-8b29-fafaf9491938", "collection_id": "", "transcript_id": "e0e5df8d-aa5d-4b9e-b266-23bac294a816"}, "text_range": {"end_pattern": null, "start_pattern": "./environment/code/README.txt
