{"text": "Starting from a repository task centered on running `pancancer_calculation.R`, the agent inspected the README and R code, identified the needed R packages (`tidyverse`, `scales`, `viridis`), and got them installed after the first attempt failed because the default R library was not writable.[T0B1:<RANGE>Run 'pancancer_calculation.R' using Rscript.</RANGE>] [T0B17:<RANGE>library(tidyverse)
library(scales)
library(viridis)</RANGE>] [T0B37:<RANGE>'lib = "/usr/local/lib/R/site-library"' is not writable</RANGE>] [T0B39:<RANGE>also installing the dependencies</RANGE>] The main challenge was a computation bug in the provided script: the direct `Rscript pancancer_calculation.R` run crashed in the `lives` calculation, because `k_cancer_test` expected an `effect` feature that the hypothetical-test data path did not define.[T0B45:<RANGE>Error in `summarize()`:
ℹ In argument: `lives = *...`.</RANGE>] [T0B49:<RANGE>lset <- gset %>% summarize(lives=value[feature == 'effect']*</RANGE>] Rather than get stuck, the agent used multiple distinct strategies: it first derived a standalone R calculation for cancers detected at 1.0% prevalence of cancer B, then wrote a patched script that regenerated the hypothetical CD plot and printed the same ranking, both showing that 90% sensitivity gives the maximum cancers detected.[T0B59] [T0B71] [T0B79:<RANGE>the sensitivity level of **90%** has the highest value on the y-axis</RANGE>] It finished by writing `report.json` with the exact requested key and value `90%`, so despite the original script not running unmodified, the run reasonably counts as a success because the answer file was produced and supported by replicated calculations and a regenerated figure.[T0B75:<RANGE>{
  "fig Report the percentage sensitivity for cancers A and B that has the highest number of cancers detected per 1,000 women for a 1.0% prevalance of cancer B.": "90%"
}</RANGE>]", "citations": [{"target": {"item": {"block_idx": 1, "item_type": "block_content", "content_idx": null, "agent_run_id": "41ad66a4-9219-479b-b917-758c1658918e", "collection_id": "", "transcript_id": "8ae1fedf-4c2b-4651-8493-01d2ad8a2aa3"}, "text_range": {"end_pattern": null, "start_pattern": "Run 'pancancer_calculation.R' using Rscript.", "target_end_idx": null, "target_start_idx": null}}, "end_idx": 358, "start_idx": 292}, {"target": {"item": {"block_idx": 17, "item_type": "block_content", "content_idx": null, "agent_run_id": "41ad66a4-9219-479b-b917-758c1658918e", "collection_id": "", "transcript_id": "8ae1fedf-4c2b-4651-8493-01d2ad8a2aa3"}, "text_range": {"end_pattern": null, "start_pattern": "library(tidyverse)
